<TD><span style="color:white">Think of consciousness like 'eyes into your mind'. Think of your mind, not so much as an ocean but a deep pool formed over aeons by the crystal water that flows in from the high snow capped mountains.<p>

Your consciousness is a set of eyes. Bobbing around somewhere in the pool.

The water in the pool is highly disturbed. Their is much in the water to cause great turbulence. The turbulent forces cause silt to rise from the bed. Visibility is thus of a very obscure nature indeed.<p>
Does this represent a somewhat reasonal metaphor? Seeing as we are not able to realise the form of our consciousness directly?

